boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Monday - Friday 9:00am-4:30pm The box office is located at the Arena (Girod Street) ground level
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: The Box Office accepts Cash, Visa, Mastercard and American Express.This may vary on some events.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Location: Box Office (Girod Street) Ground Level How Soon: 2 hours prior to showtime. New Orleans Pelicans: 90 mins prior to tip-off. The customer must present actual credit card, picture ID, and confirmation number.

venues.parkingDetail: Parking is available in the Superdome and nearby parking garages. Charges vary. Superdome Parking Info: (504) 587-3805

generalInfo.generalRule: Items not allowed: NO Video cameras or Audio recorders; NO Weapons; NO Outside food, cans, or bottles; NO iPads Smoking Policy: Smoking is ONLY allowed on the North and East smoking balcony NO SMOKING is allowed in the seating areas !! Lost/Stolen Tickets: There is NO replacement for LOST tickets. Stolen ticket replacement requests MUST be accompanied by a police report
generalInfo.childRule: There is no age limit for events at the Arena. Children UNDER 2 years old are admitted free without occupying a seat. This may vary on some events.

venues.parkingDetail: Ramp parking is available in attached KeyBank Center Ramp and LECOM Harborcenter Ramp. Surface lot parking is available on Mississippi St & Baltimore Street. https://keybankcenter.com/page/parking

generalInfo.generalRule: A complete guide to arena policies and procedures can be found at https://keybankcenter.com on the General Info and Plan Your Visit tabs.
generalInfo.childRule: Adults wishing to bring a child ages 3 and under to a Buffalo Sabres or Buffalo Bandits must stop in the Account Services Office located next to the ticket windows in the KeyBank Center pavilion on their way into the game to have the child wrist banded. All children 2 years of age and over need a ticket to all other events (concerts, family shows, etc). Wrist Band will not be for a seat, but allows the child to sit on the lap of a parent or guardian.
